"Hello good morning Army, kaise hain aap sab log?"
"Aaj ka topic bahut hi IMPORTANT hai â€“ Decimal aur Binary conversion."

Sir:
"Is lecture me sirf formula ya math nahi, hum sochna seekhenge."
"Math â†’ Logic â†’ Code, teenon clear hone chahiye."

====================================================================
*/

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
/*
====================================================================
1ï¸âƒ£ NUMBER SYSTEM BASICS (Sir Board Explanation)
====================================================================

Decimal Number System:
Base = 10
Digits = 0 se 9

Binary Number System:
Base = 2
Digits = sirf 0 aur 1

Sir:
"Computer ko sirf 0 aur 1 samajh aata hai."
"Isliye hume decimal ko binary me convert karna padta hai."

====================================================================
*/


/*
====================================================================
2ï¸âƒ£ DECIMAL â†’ BINARY (PURE THINKING FIRST)
====================================================================

Sir:
"Binary nikalne ke liye ek hi kaam repeat hota hai."

Steps:
1. number % 2  â†’ remainder (last binary digit)
2. number / 2  â†’ quotient (next number)
3. Jab tak number > 0, repeat

Example: number = 13

13 % 2 = 1
6  % 2 = 0
3  % 2 = 1
1  % 2 = 1

Sir:
"Remainders hamesha REVERSE order me aate hain."
"Isliye hume unhe ulta jodna padta hai."

Binary (reverse): 1101
====================================================================
*/

int number;
cout << "Enter decimal number: ";
cin >> number;

int remainder;
int binaryAnswer = 0;   // final binary number
int multiply = 1;       // 1, 10, 100, 1000 ...

while (number > 0)
{
    remainder = number % 2;      // last bit
    number = number / 2;         // quotient

    // Reverse order fix:
    // Pehle aaya bit â†’ ones place
    // Agla bit â†’ tens place, etc.
    binaryAnswer = remainder * multiply + binaryAnswer;
    multiply = multiply * 10;
}

cout << "Binary = " << binaryAnswer << endl;


/*
====================================================================
3ï¸âƒ£ DECIMAL â†’ BINARY (BITWISE VERSION â€“ SIR TRICK)
====================================================================

Sir:
"Computer ke level pe %2 aur /2 bhi bitwise se hota hai."

Rules:
number % 2  ==  number & 1
number / 2  ==  number >> 1

Sir:
"Agar bitwise samajh gaye, to low-level coding strong ho jaegi."
====================================================================
*/

int n;
cout << "\nEnter decimal again (bitwise method): ";
cin >> n;

int bitBinary = 0;
int place = 1;

while (n)
{
    int bit = n & 1;              // last bit
    bitBinary = bit * place + bitBinary;
    place = place * 10;
    n = n >> 1;                   // divide by 2
}

cout << "Binary (bitwise) = " << bitBinary << endl;


/*
====================================================================
4ï¸âƒ£ BINARY â†’ DECIMAL (REVERSE PROCESS)
====================================================================

Sir:
"Ab hum ulta karenge â€“ Binary se Decimal."

Logic:
Har digit ko 2 ki power se multiply karo.

Example: 1101

= 1Ã—2^0 + 0Ã—2^1 + 1Ã—2^2 + 1Ã—2^3
= 1 + 0 + 4 + 8
= 13

Sir:
"Binary ka last digit sabse chhoti power hoti hai."
====================================================================
*/

int binary;
cout << "\nEnter binary number: ";
cin >> binary;

int digit;
int decimalAnswer = 0;
int power = 1;   // 2^0

while (binary > 0)
{
    digit = binary % 10;     // last binary digit
    binary = binary / 10;    // remove last digit

    decimalAnswer = digit * power + decimalAnswer;
    power = power * 2;       // next power of 2
}

cout << "Decimal = " << decimalAnswer << endl;


/*
====================================================================
5ï¸âƒ£ IMPORTANT WARNINGS (Sir ne class me bataya)
====================================================================

âš ï¸ Binary number int me store ho raha hai
âš ï¸ int sirf 32-bit ka hota hai
âš ï¸ Agar binary length > 31 bits hui â†’ overflow
âš ï¸ Isliye large binary ka output galat aa sakta hai

Sir:
"Ye galti code ki nahi, MEMORY LIMIT ki hoti hai."

Solution (future lectures):
âœ” String use karenge
âœ” Arrays / vectors use karenge

====================================================================
*/


/*
====================================================================
6ï¸âƒ£ NEGATIVE NUMBERS KYUN SKIP KIYE?
====================================================================

Sir:
"Negative binary simple nahi hota."
"2â€™s complement use hota hai."

Reason:
âœ” Sign bit
âœ” Complement + 1
âœ” Direct int logic fail ho jata hai

Sir:
"Strings aur bit-level understanding ke baad hi karenge."
====================================================================
*/


/*
====================================================================
7ï¸âƒ£ THINKING / HOMEWORK (VERY IMPORTANT)
====================================================================

Sir:
"Socho aur analyse karo:"

1. Large binary kyu overflow karta hai?
2. -13 binary me kaise store hota hai?
3. Left shift = multiply by 2 kyun?
4. Right shift = divide by 2 kyun?

"Ratta nahi, LOGIC build karo."
====================================================================
*/


/*
====================================================================
